	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Hout Bay police are looking for suspects involved in the
shooting of a taxi driver today, Wednesday 21 November at about 07:35. According to police spokesperson, Warrant Officer Tanya
Lesch, the driver was shot in the arms and legs. “He sustained gunshot wounds to his arms and legs. He is
currently receiving hospital treatment. Police are following up all leads.” Lesch says police have not made any arrests yet. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  